FT  04 FEB 93 / Observer: Official
Whitehall's war against the English language continues. The Office of Public
Service and Science in the Cabinet Office has announced that William
Waldegrave 'is tasked by the prime minister, with identifying areas of
excessive secrecy in government and to carry forward the moves already under
way across government towards greater openness'. Perhaps it's time for a
discreet silence on educational standards.
